The map below shows the estimated number of deaths by type: natural and man-made. One is estimated to have been caused by Barack Obama et al. from Haiti, as well the 44 killed by me in Nebraska. As we know for certain, our own Barack Obama caused 86 earthquake deaths (including 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012, and 2013, with a total average of 217 per year). Luckily, among the last part of his presidency, in 2016, the number of natural disasters has risen with a total of ZERO, according to the World Bank Disaster Risk Database.
